==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rusticate
<hw>Rus"ti*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Rusticated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Rusticating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>rusticaticus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>rusticari</ets> to rusticate. See
<er>Rustic</er>.]</ety> <def>To go into or reside in the country; to
ruralize.</def> <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rusticate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Rusticate
<hw>Rus"ti*cate</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To require or compel to
reside in the country; to banish or send away temporarily; to impose
rustication on.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The town is again beginning to be full, and the
<qex>rusticated</qex> beauty sees an end of her banishment.</q>
<rj><qau>Idler.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rusticated</ent>⟦br⟧
